# ============================================================
# CONFIDENCE & NEXT STEPS
# ============================================================

# As-of 2026-05-03, the bulk of routing evidence is L4 (vendor blogs +
# leaderboards). Per mizaj 11 L4 ceiling = 0.40, the routing claims
# above bound the joint at @0.40 unless lifted by:
#   - L1 own-measurement (we'd need to run our own slice — costs $)
#   - L3 peer-reviewed (requires academic publication of these benchmarks)
#   - Multi-source convergence (mutawatir adjustment): some claims have
#     2-3 independent sources and could lift to 0.85 ceiling per mizaj 14
#
# The deepseek long-context claim (L1 cheapllm own-measurement) is the
# strongest single-claim anchor and shows what L1 routing rules look like.

# What's documented but UNTESTED in cheapcode's own measurements:
#   - haiku-4.5 quality on bounded code (operator memory says yes;
#     no in-house cheapcode receipt yet)
#   - opus-4.7 SWE-bench-Pro lead (vendor benchmark only)
#   - GPT-5.5 closed-book hallucination rate (vendor-derived)
#   - Gemini 3 Flash GPQA 90.4% (vendor blog only)
#
# Atom 0011 (smallest distinguishing experiment) suggests: when we want
# to lift any L4 → L1, the smallest distinguishing test is to run a
# focused 5-10 task probe of the specific routing claim, not a generic
# "wrapper-vs-baseline" comparison.
